job_detail:
Summary:
Super Micro Computer, Inc. is looking for System Thermal Manager, who is full of passion and is willing to learn. Detail-oriented, responsible and dedicated attitude, and an outgoing personality are traits highly preferred. The position will be in charge of server thermal design and validations.

Duties:
• Conceptualize, plan, and execute the design and development of cooling solutions for server platforms; 
• Verify thermal compliance of systems and components with regards to industry standards; 
• Manage thermal team for measurements and analysis of cooling systems and components; 
• Manage and present lab results to engineering teams, vendors, and customers; 
• Investigate and identify new techniques to advance thermal developments and validations; 
• Collaborate with HW, ME, Lab and PM teams for system designs and environmental tests; 
• Interface with contract vendors for product developments and improvement recommendations

other:
• BA/MS in ME/Aerospace Engineering or equivalent training with minimum 3+ years related experience; 
• Experience working as a thermal, mechanical, or validation engineer in computer or electronics cooling development; 
• Computer system level thermal testing or validation experience including thermocouple installations, automated data acquisitions, and related lab equipment operations; 
• Experience in heat sink and air shroud/fan duct designs, cooling fan/blower selections; 
• Experience in liquid-cooling solution design of server product or liquid-cooling  integration of datacenter.
• Experience in system thermal simulation via Flotherm / Flotherm XT / STAR CCM+. 
• Excellent verbal and communication skills.

